txt.en: 'Bah! I shall return, and next time in greater strength!'
'You fought gloriously, [placeholder]! We have defended Aughaire and routed the forces of Angmar. I feel the tide is turning against Mordirith!'
'If not for these weaklings I would have had my revenge!'
'Quickly now, we must return to Gath Forthnír and see if there we are needed elsewhere.'
Instance: The Battle for Aughaire
'Aughaire is not yet saved! I shall return and have my revenge!'

'I will not fall today! I shall yet have my revenge on the Trév Gallorg!

'We must hurry, [placeholder]! Angmar's host is nearly here.

'We must protect all of the bulwarks of Aughaire, or we will be unable to defend the town. When the call rings out, move to help defend that bulwark. I will keep watch over the Gate of Aughaire, in case any sneak past our defences.

'Go now and defend the good people of Aughaire!'
